Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Next to Crows Nest Metro Station

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Located just a few doors up from the future Crows Nest Metro station, 437-441 Pacific Highway Crows Nest is a two-storey freehold mixed-use building with potential development upside (STCA). The property currently acts as a valuable pedestrian arcade through to the Crows Nest Village, with 9 tenancies providing a diversified income with the benefit of staggered expiries and short-term upside through leasing up vacancy and rental reversion. Being so close to the future Crows Nest Metro Station, the property is included in the St Leonards & Crows Nest 2036 Plan which provides a significant development opportunity allowing for a potential GFA of 1,617sqm (STCA).

437-441 Pacific Highway benefits from the following key attributes:
- Huge 30m* Frontage
- Net income of $111,775 per annum*
- Leased to multiple tenancies
- Mixed use commercial freehold building on popular Pacific Highway
- Net lettable area of 645sqm* with high vehicular and pedestrian exposure
- Set to benefit from the St Leonards and Crows Nest Station 2036 Final Plan
- Situated metres from Crows Nest Village, St Leonards Station and future Crows Nest Metro
- Located within proximity to parks, shops, local restaurants and amenities

For sale via private treaty

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.
*Approximate
Note: All financial figures have been provided by the Vendor. Purchasers are advised to conduct their own independent due diligence.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: FREEHOLD INVESTMENT WITH POTENTIAL DEVELOPMENT UPSIDE

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
67 West Street is located on the corner of Carlow and West Streets with easy access to North Sydney, Crows Nest and Neutral Bay.  It has a excellence presence on the corner with two sides of natural light through large windows and good signage exposure.

The space has floor boards, a storage area, own bathroom and kitchen as well as access to a courtyard and a parking space.

This is a perfect opportunity for a retailer or commercial user to take advantage of a great location in a boutique style building and have your own identity.

Don't hesitate to arrange an inspection, call Lisa Treble on 0411 542 497 or Michael Arcus on 0438 550 967.

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Adjacent to the future Crows Nest Metro

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE, as the exclusive sales agent, is pleased to present 2-4 Clarke Street, Crows Nest. This mixed use freehold building includes two retail shops, two storeys of office space and 16 undercover car spaces. Located adjacent to the future metro station development and metres from the popular Willoughby Road retail and dining strip, the property is guaranteed to capitalise on the future growth of the St Leonards and Crows Nest priority precinct as well as proposed increased planning controls.

2-4 Clarke Street, Crows Nest benefits from the following attributes:

-	Mixed use asset with multiple income streams
-	Adjacent to the future Crows Nest Metro Station Development
-	NLA: 1,088sqm*
-	Site area: 556sqm*
-	Estimated fully leased net market income: $520,584 per annum*
-	Significant rental reversion or development opportunity
-	Proposed FSR of 4.5:1 & height limit of 8 storeys
-	Located at the centre of the St Leonards & Crows Nest Priority Precinct
-	Metres from Willoughby Road retail & dining strip

2-4 Clarke Street, Crows Nest is being sold via expressions of interest closing on Wednesday, 24 April 2019 at 4.00pm.

For further information, please contact the exclusive sales agents.

*Approximate

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: LOWER NORTH SHORE FREEHOLD OFFICE INVESTMENT

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Close to new Crows Nest Metro Station

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE is pleased to present 3-5 Rodborough Avenue, Crows Nest. Located in Sydney’s Lower North Shore, this is an extremely rare opportunity to secure a desirable development site well positioned to take advantage of the incoming Sydney Metro Train project.

3-5 Rodborough Avenue, Crows Nest benefits from the following key attributes:

•	Site area 1,100sqm* 
•	Quiet cul-de-sac location two traffic lights from Sydney CBD
•	FlexibleR4 High Density Residential zoning allowing for a residential flat building (apartments), multi dwelling housing (townhouses), and shop top housing (STCA)
•	12m building height limit
•	Current improvements of a six-bedroom house and 28 place child care centre
•	Currently benefiting from holding income
•	Potential net holding income of $159,973 per annum*
•	Surrounded by a wealth of educational institutions and health services
•	Well positioned to benefit from the new Crows Nest Sydney Metro Station
•	Located 150m* from St Leonards Park, 400m* from Warringah Freeway entry, 600m* from Woolworths and 1.4km* from North Sydney CBD

3-5 Rodborough Road will be offered for sale via expressions of interest closing on Wednesday 08 August 2018 at 4:00pm.
